snippet.title: Hoo - Harshdeep Kaur
snippet.description:
A 400 year old kalaam originally composed by Sultan Bahu, a Sufi saint who belonged to the Awan tribe, sung by his followers and Sufi practitioners in Pakistan and Punjab since ages.
Music conceived and created by Lesle Lewis. www.leslelewis.com. Instrumentalist: Zoheb-Keyboard, Darshan-Drums, Nyzel-Electric Guitar, Dibyajyoti-Bass Guitar, Sanjoy-accoustic, Arun-Percussion. Lyrics: Sultan Bahu

snippet.title: 'Khuda Wohi Hai' - Zila Khan, Coke Studio @ MTV Season 2
snippet.description:
Credits:

Produced by: Zila Khan
Language: Hindi
Vocals: Zila Khan
Keys: Jarvis Menezes
Bass: Nyzel D'Lima
Guitar: Sanjay Joseph
Percussion: Sanket Athale

Recorded by: Steve Fitzmaurice, Ashish Manchanda, assisted by Thorsten Muller
Mixed & Mastered by Ashish Manchanda at Flying Carpet Productions, Mumbai

Lyrics:

Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti
Chalaa raha hai
Wohi Khuda Hai
Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti

Dhikhayi bhi jo, na de nazar bhi
Jo aa raha hai
Wohi Khuda Hai
Wohi Khuda Hai (3)
Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti

Nazar bhi rakhe, samaate bhi
Woh jaan leta hai, niyatein bhi
Nazar bhi rakhe, samaate bhi
Woh jaan leta hai, niyatein bhi

Jo khana ae la shagoor mein 
Jagmagaa raha hai
Wohi Khuda Hai
Wohi Khuda Hai (3)
Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti

Haan talaash usko, karo sabhi mein
Woh hai badalti hui ruton mein
Talaash usko, karo sabhi mein
Woh hai badalti hui ruton mein

Jo sabke haathon pe mohre kudrat
Lagaa raha hai
Wohi Khuda Hai
Wohi Khuda Hai (3)

Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti
Chalaa raha hai
Wohi Khuda Hai
Wohi to hai jo, Nizaam-e-hasti

Meaning:
The song is a beautiful expression by an Urdu Poet, Muzaffar Warsi of the fact that there is a higher power that controls the order of life; and that this invisible force... is God. 
For He is beautifully managing the entire existence and is regulating all creations, but never ever takes any credits. It is God, who beautifully paves way for life to go on smoothly and balances it all, by keeping a constant vigil on his creations. He is the one who illuminates our souls and minds.

He is Omnipresent and hence cannot be found in physical forms. He is indeed the conductor of the symphony of all seasons and is the music of life in each heart. He is God, He is God...

snippet.title: 'Haq Maula' - Dhruv Sangari & The Humble Mystic, Coke Studio @ MTV Season 2
snippet.description:
It's a song in praise of Imam Ali, a sufi song that has been reinterpreted over years by many great musicians. This was Dhruv's attempt to make a sensible fusion of Indian and Western instruments only for Coke Studio @ MTV. Featured instruments include a string trio of mandolin, guitar and israj.

Credits:

Produced & Rearranged by: Dhruv Sangari & The Humble Mystic
Language: Hindi
Lyrics: Traditional & poem by Saim Chishti 
Vocals: Dhruv Sangari
Drums: Abhinav Dhar
Guitar: Saibal Basu
Bass: Anirban Ghosh
Keys: Anil Chawla
Tabla: Amjad Khan
Mandolin: Siraj Khan
Harmonium: Salamat Ali
Israj: Arshad Khan

Recorded by: Steve Fitzmaurice, Ashish Manchanda, assisted by Thorsten Muller
Mixed & Mastered by Ashish Manchanda at Flying Carpet Productions, Mumbai

Lyrics:
Ali Shah e Mardan Imam ul Kabira,
Ke baad az Nabi shud Bashir ul Nazira

Ali Maula Ali Maula Ali Maula
Khuloos e dil se Ali ka jo naam leta hai,
Khuloos e dil se Ali ka jo naam leta hai,
Vohi toh lazzat e umr e dawaam leta hai,
Vohi toh lazzat e umr e dawaam leta hai,
Khuda ke bandon suno ghaur se Khuda ki qasam,
Khuda ke bandon suno ghaur se Khuda ki qasam,
Ali ka naam to girton ko thaam leta hai

Ali Maula Ali Maula Ali Maula

Kitnay teer unki, Kitnay teer unki Nigaahon ke utaaroon dil mein,
Kitnay teer unki Nigaahon ke utaaroon dil mein,
Deeda e shauq ne daala hai ajab mushkil mein,
Deeda e shauq ne daala hai ajab mushkil mein,
Tu hi Tu hai mere ehsaas ki har manzil mein,
Tu hi Tu hai mere ehsaas ki har manzil mein,
Jiska jo hota hai rakhta hai ussi se nisbat,
Jiska jo hota hai rakhta hai ussi se nisbat,
Meray Maula mujhe yaad aayen har ik mushkil mein

Ali Maula Ali Maula Ali Maula

Unki Saim hai, Unki Saim hai miladat ki jagah Haram e Kaba,
Unki Saim hai, Unki Saim hai miladat ki jagah Haram e Kaba,
Aankh kholi toh, aankh kholi toh Chehra e Muhammad dekha,
Aankh kholi toh Chehra e Muhammad dekha,
Noor e Tanveer Ali Noor e Tanveer Ali
Badr e Muneer Ali, Badr e Muneer Ali,
Maalik e Taqdeer Ali

Haq Ali Ali Ali Maula Ali Ali
Ali Maula Ali Maula Ali Maula

Meaning:
Poet writes these words in praise of Hazrat Imam Ali. He says that, Ali was not only brave and was a great leader, but he was also, as noble as the Prophet. Hence anyone who sincerely prays to him gets his blessings to live and relish life to the fullest...for he is a great guide to the seeking souls.
He is the brightest of all and is an enlightened one, thus being in his strong presence, is as good as being in a holy place.

snippet.title: 'Dum Dum' - Shilpa Rao, Ashvin Mani Sharma & Ash Roy, Coke Studio @ MTV Season 2
snippet.description:
Dum Dum is a song of hope and belief in life through its nicest and toughest times. It's about keeping the faith that everything always works out in the end. No matter what life puts us through we still should have faith in things we believe. Belief in love, truth and freedom after all are the true signs of a bohemian!

This optimism is expressed through ethnic Punjabi lyrics, where the phonetics lends itself perfectly to the pulse of the song. Jalebee Cartel's live electronica inclusion further adds a positive kick to the song.

Credits:

Composer: Shilpa Rao
Producer: Shilpa Rao, Ashvin Mani Sharma & Ash Roy (Jalebee Cartel)
Language: Punjabi
Lyrics: Shellee
Vocals: Shilpa Rao & Arun Daga
Electronics: Ashvin Mani Sharma
Electric Percussion: Ash Roy
Drums: Ashwin
Guitar: Aditya Shankar
Guitar: Gaurav Gupta
Bass: Johan Pais
Percussion: Arun Solanki
Keys: Hitesh Modak
Sarangi: Dilshad Khan

Recorded by: Steve Fitzmaurice, Ashish Manchanda, assisted by Thorsten Muller
Mixed & Mastered by Ashish Manchanda at Flying Carpet Productions, Mumbai

Lyrics:
Chad yaana khaida mera ishqe ne, chadde ya na
Labbe yaana rus ke o kaad da geya, labbe yaana
Laagi na heena na vanga paaiyan
Zaar zaar royi na haakan laiya
Chadde yaana khaida mera ishqe ne, chadde ya na

Meaning:
Dum Dum is a beautiful song lyrically capturing a heartening truth in life and that is, none of us are ever alone. 
Life may not be a bed of roses for all and everything in our lives may not be as perfect and as we wished, but along all its twists and turns, there is someone high above, always guarding and guiding us with love and care.

If we only believe in this Eternal Truth, will our life be a carefree and an enjoyable journey. A journey with no baggage no complains and no worries of being lonely or helpless...but with true faith, love and freedom!

Where will you run today O Krishna!!

snippet.title: 'Chhalla' - Hari & Sukhmani, Coke Studio @ MTV Season 2
snippet.description:
This is a reinterpretation of a Punjabi folk song about a boy meeting his lover by the well. In those days mixing of the sexes was not very common and lovers were always in the lookout for a private spot where they could meet. Invariably, that spot was by the village well. The song talks about the anticipation felt by the lovers before meeting and the sense of elation that follows. 

For CS@MTV Season2, this song has been re-interpreted with a dub step feel and the addition of Middle Eastern percussion and Israaj. 

Credits:

Composer: Traditional composition
Produced & Performed by: Hari & Sukhmani
Language: Punjabi
Lyrics: Traditional
Percussion: Fakhroddin Ghaffari
Israj: Arshad Khan
Recorded by: Steve Fitzmaurice, Ashish Manchanda, assisted by Thorsten Muller
Mixed & Mastered by Ashish Manchanda at Flying Carpet Productions, Mumbai

Now get Coca-Cola delivered home. To order, click https://www.coke2home.com/buy-coca-cola/

Lyrics:
Jaavo ni koi mod liyavoh,
Ni mere naal gaya ajj ladd ke,
Hoye allah karey jey aa jaave sohna,
Devaan jaan kadmaan vich rakh ke.

Ho Challa beri boohey, ve vatan mahi da door ey,
Ve jaana pehle poor ey, vey gall sun challeya
Chora ve kahda laya ee johraa.

Challa khooh tey dhariye,
Khooh tey dhariye,
Challa khooh tey dhariye,
Challa khooh tey dhariye,
Challa khooh tey dhariye,
Ve Gallan mooh tey kariye,
Ve sacchey rabb ton dariye,
Ve gall sun challeya,
Chhora ve kahda laya ee johra.

Allah beli, O mera Maula beli,
O mera Allah beli, mera Maula beli (4)

Challa kaaliyan mirchan,
Kaaliyan mirchan,
Challa kaaliyan mirchan,
Challa kaaliyan mirchan,
Challa kaaliyan mirchan,
Ve mohra pee ke marsaan,
Ve sire tere o chadsaan,
Ve gall sun challeya,
Chhora Ve saad key keeta ee kola.

Allah beli, O mera Maula beli,
O mera Allah beli, mera Maula beli (4)

Challa gall di gaani,
Challa gall di gaani,
Challa gall di gaani,
Challa gall di gaani,
Ve tur gaye dilllan dey jaani
Ve meri dukhaan di kahani
Ve aa key sun ja
Chhora ve kahda laya ee jora.

Allah beli, O mera Maula beli,
O mera Allah beli, mera Maula beli (4)

Jaavo ni koi mod liyavoh

Meaning:
Love is a colorful and a beautiful feeling. But it does have its bitter-sweet moments. The song beautifully expresses the helplessness of a lover, after one of those bitter moments (over a trivial issue) is imploring her lover to come back. 
"Challa", is originally a very touching and a sweet Punjabi folk song. The Poet through these lyrics paints the lover in his various moods and also beautifully captures the drama of her relationship with him. 
It's interesting how a person you love can give you so much joy and at the same time, cause so much pain. When the going is smooth, everything seems like a beautiful and seamless dream... but as soon as it gets tested (for its strength and depth), everything seems dark and unclear. 
The song in many words captures the fact that, while love can empower someone, it can also leave one helpless...

With every passage, the Poet expresses her longing to meet her love. The separation is so unbearable that she implores the Almighty, to protect her lover and her relationship...

Download this song NOW!
http://www.itunes.com/cokestudio
